# Git workflow

- Every code change must end in a commit and a push. Never leave finished work uncommitted in the working tree.
- Never commit directly on `main`. Create a branch first: `feat/<scope>`, `fix/<scope>`, `chore/<scope>`, or `docs/<scope>`.
- Use Conventional Commits scoped by service or area, matching repo history, e.g. `feat(transaction-service): add ledger reversal endpoint`.
- Group changes into logical commits (one concern per commit); do not dump the whole working tree into one commit.
- After pushing the branch, merge it into `main` with a merge commit (`--no-ff`, consistent with existing history) and push `main`.
- Before committing: review the diff, drop accidental changes, and never commit secrets, real `.env` files, or personal financial data.
